company.name: Lifeline Children's Services
company.description:
Lifeline Children's Services is a domestic and international ministry reaching out to vulnerable children through adoption, orphan care, foster care, and the Gospel.

Lifeline Children’s Services is a non-profit 501c3 ministry and licensed agency founded in 1981. Lifeline promotes the sanctity of life through ministry to young women in the midst of unplanned pregnancy, domestic and international adoption services, foster care, and orphan care through (un)adopted. 

Since its founding, Lifeline’s commitment has remained focused on working with Christian families, to ensure that children are raised with the truth of who Jesus Christ is as their Lord and Savior. Lifeline currently has offices in 10 states.
